A Missouri family is celebrating giving birth to rare identical triplets, bringing their family to seven.

But two weeks after the arrival of their daughters - Sonja, Sylvia and Scarlett - on March 19,  Laura and Brad Partridge are still unable to tell the girls apart, so they have devised a nifty plan.

'Everyone has a signature colour,' Laura, from Des Peres, told MailOnline. 'Pink for Scarlett, purple for Sylvia and yellow for Sonja, and they have corresponding outfits.

'A 
friend is even getting me non-toxic nail polish for their toenails so that 
way we know for sure who's who in the middle of the night or during a 
bath.'

