The babies will remain in intensive care at Mercy Children's Hospital
until they have reached certain feeding and weight goals, which doctors
believe will be around their original due date of May 10.

Despite being born seven weeks early, they all weighed three pounds and are doing well.

'We are doing excellently,' said 34-year-old Laura, who left hospital a week ago. 'We are overjoyed that every one is so well.'

The
Partridges, who also have a three-year-old son, Stephen, and a 
17-month-old daughter, Stella, had feared that the story would not be 
such a happy one.

